# Digest allowlist for every source tarball CI downloads and executes.
#
# HTTPS protects the transport, not the origin: a compromised mirror, a mutable
# re-cut release, or a poisoned Actions cache all survive it. Every tarball is
# verified against this file before it is extracted, and an unknown version is
# a hard failure rather than a silent trust decision.
#
# Each digest below was verified once against the upstream PGP signature (the
# tarball's .asc, checked with the upstream signing key) before being recorded.
#
# Format: <sha256>  <tarball basename>
